      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It is completely normal to feel uncomfortable when a neighbor changes their Wi-Fi name to something so personal, though there is no evidence they are using it to track your location. Wi-Fi signal movement alone doesn't constitute tracking, as such activity typically requires specialized hardware or software specifically designed for surveillance. For peace of mind, you can try changing your own router's password, ensuring your device's location services are secure, or simply moving slightly to change how the signal reflects off your phone's coordinates.",
