      "content": "Yes, noticing strong signal fluctuations specifically in certain rooms can feel unsettling, but Wi-Fi triangulation by itself doesn't reveal your precise location or track your movements without dedicated tracking software. Since Wi-Fi is not Bluetooth, it cannot detect when you are inside your own home, and the fields in your wall are acting as the primary factor. Your experience likely stems from normal signal physics rather than hidden surveillance.",
